[[File:PolKommunarka2.jpg|right|thumb|The gate]] The '''Communarka''' or '''Kommunarka''' ({{lang-ru|Расстрельный полигон «Коммунарка»}}) was the site of [[NKVD]] mass shootings from 1937 to 1941 in the [[Novomoskovsky Administrative Okrug]] south-west of the centre of [[Moscow]]. It is now an [[Russian Orthodox Church|Orthodox cemetery]]. According to the [[Federal Security Service]], 10,000 people were killed and buried there.<ref> [http://izvestia.ru/news/329601 Спецобъект "Монастырь"] izvestia.ru. </ref>
