{{Unreferenced|date=July 2010}} The '''Perpetual Accord''' is a peace treaty and alliance of the [[Acht Orte]] of the [[Old Swiss Confederacy]] and [[Duke Sigismund]] of Austria. [[King Louis XI]] of France was elected as a mediator between both parties. The negotiations took place in [[Constance]]. The first version was finalized on 30 March 1474, but had to wait until early 1475 for the ratification of the final version.
